\": \"path=app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/repository/LoginRepositoryImpl.kt; category=kotlin-source; importance=critical; classes=LoginRepositoryImpl, PrefsDataStore; keyMethods=toggleLoginState; featurePoint=Observable state, ViewModel/Flow/LiveData/recomposition, or UI state propagation.\",\n4027:       \"status\": \"implemented-simplified\",\n4028:       \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-02-startup-navigation-session\",\n4029:       \"sourceBehavior\": \"LoginRepositoryImpl exposes `loginState` as a `Flow<Boolean>` that SplashViewModel reads to determine the startup route before clearing loading state.\",\n4030:       \"targetBehavior\": \"Phase 02 keeps the user-visible startup-state behavior with a synchronous preference read plus `StartupStore` mutable route state instead of a long-lived observable preference stream. The initial route still resolves from the persisted login flag before the shell becomes interactive.\",\n4031:       \"verificationEvidence\": [\n4032:         \"Manual code review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState feeds entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj::StartupStore.resolveStartRoute.\",\n4033:         \"Manual code review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj::resolveStartRoute centralizes the persisted-flag-to-route mapping used by the startup store and tests.\",\n4034:         \"Test verification: translation-inputs/test-build-reports/phase-02-startup-navigation-session/test-build-report.md recorded PASS for `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos`, including startup-route assertions in entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj.\"\n4035:       ],\n4036:       \"parityLevel\": \"simplified\",\n4037:       \"targetEndpoints\": [\n4038:         \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.read